# Loupe code ownership
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request review from the listed owners
# when a pull request touches matching paths. It is also the file that
# the "Require review from Code Owners" branch-protection toggle on
# `main` consults — without a CODEOWNERS file, that toggle is a no-op
# and OpenSSF Scorecard's Branch-Protection check flags the repo.
#
# Syntax reference:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Loupe is a single-maintainer project; every path currently resolves
# to the same owner. As co-maintainers join, add more specific rules
# above the catch-all — later matches win.

# Catch-all: everything in the repo is owned by the maintainer.
*                               @Sam-Dowling

# Source tree — the hand-written code that ships in docs/index.html.
/src/                           @Sam-Dowling

# Build + maintenance tooling.
/scripts/                       @Sam-Dowling
/make.py                        @Sam-Dowling

# Vendored third-party libraries. Any change here is a supply-chain
# event and must rotate the SHA-256 pin in VENDORED.md.
/vendor/                        @Sam-Dowling
/VENDORED.md                    @Sam-Dowling

# Repo automation: CI, CodeQL, Scorecard, Dependabot, issue templates.
/.github/                       @Sam-Dowling

# Security-relevant docs and config.
/SECURITY.md                    @Sam-Dowling
/eslint.config.mjs              @Sam-Dowling
